author: kfogel
msg: Add some new test data to reveal a bug in cvs2svn's deletion handling.
The bug is that when 'partial-prune/trunk/sub/first' is deleted,
cvs2svn.py prunes 'partial-prune/trunk', which is incorrect for two
reasons: one, 'partial-prune/trunk/sub/second' still exists, and two,
even if pruning *were* supposed to happen here, it should happen to
'partial-prune/' itself, not a subdir, since the top-level file
'partial-prune/permanent' isn't yet born by the time the other two
files get removed.
All in branches/cvs2svn-kfogel/:
* tools/cvs2svn/cvs2svn.py: Add more debugging prints.
* tools/cvs2svn/test-data/main-cvsrepos/partial-prune/: New data.  The
dates in permanent,v will actually need to be adjusted so that the
file already exists by the time both sub/first and sub/second are
removed.  However, right now, having the dates so far in the
future is convenient because it allows the more serious bug
described above to show itself.  When we do adjust them, we should
make another test dir similar to partial-prune/ that keeps the
current dates, so we can test that the top directory gets readded
correctly when 'permanent' appears).
